			<h1><span class="less"><a href="index.html">SLE 2008</a> paper:</span><br><i>Practical Scope Recovery Using Bridge Parsing</i></h1>
			<h2><a href="../profile/EmmaNilssonNyman.html">Emma Nilsson-Nyman</a>, <a href="../profile/TorbjörnEkman.html">Torbjörn Ekman</a>, <a href="../profile/GörelHedin.html">Görel Hedin</a></h2>
<ul><li>DOI: <a href="https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_7">10.1007/978-3-642-00434-6_7</a></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t1b.html"><span class="tagM">T1B: Static Semantics</span></a><ul><li> It targets scope recovery/name-binding—key aspects of static semantics—in the presence of incomplete or legacy code.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4a.html"><span class="tagL">T4A: Workbenches</span></a><ul><li> It contributes a practical parsing/analysis technique intended to support IDEs and analysis tools.
</li></ul></li>
<li><a href="../tag/t4c.html"><span class="tagL">T4C: Vertical Transformation</span></a><ul><li> Scope recovery supports recovery of structure/meaning from existing artifacts.
</li></ul></li></ul>
